name: frozen fish sticks production, hake | frozen fish sticks, hake | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20899/documentation

This activity represents the processing of a multi-ingredient hake product, referred to as fish sticks or fish fingers, at a fish processing factory. The main product is fish blocks of Patagonian grenadier (Macrunorus magellanicus). These fish blocks are marine freighted and once they arrive at the port"s premises, they are delivered in refrigerated lorries to the processing plant. Two other important products are breadcrumbs and a wheat flour mix that are used in the battering. These are produced in a mill near the seafood processing plant and transported by truck. 

Seafood processing factory in SouthWest Europe activities include the reception of hake fish blocks and their processing until they are transformed into fish fingers in a multi-ingredient final product. 

Distribution from factory to wholesalers was excluded. Packaging is excluded. Packaging in this particular product is constituted by 22.98 grams of carton and 1.17 grams of polyethylene.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/107:Manufacture of other food products/1075:Manufacture of prepared meals and dishes

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data were collected for average conditions in year 2011.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data collected at a processing plant in NW Spain. Fish blocks marine freighted from Latin America to a port in NW Spain and then transported by truck to the processing plant. Two other important products are breadcrumbs and a wheat flour mix that are used in the battering. These are produced in a mill near the seafood processing plant and transported by truck.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Mainly with machinery. Manual process is limited to detecting amorphous fish sticks that are separated prior to packaging.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data were reported by technical staff at the seafood processing industry.

exchanges.description: 323.47 grams of fish sticks is the mass content of the ten (10)  fish sticks (i.e., fish fingers) contained in one cardboard package ready for distribution and sale. The package itself weighs 25.97 grams.
